<div class="simple-item-view-authors item-page-field-wrapper table">
<h5>Author(s)</h5>
<div class="ds-dc_contributor_author-authority">Segal, Theodore D.</div>
</div>
<div class="item-page-field-wrapper">
<h5>Language</h5>English</div>
<div class="simple-item-view-show-full item-page-field-wrapper table">
<a href="/handle/20.500.12657/51885?show=full">Show full item record</a>
</div>
</div>
<div class="col-sm-8">
<div class="simple-item-view-description item-page-field-wrapper table">
<h5 class="visible-xs">Abstract</h5>
<div>Theodore D. Segal narrates the fraught and contested fight for racial justice at Duke University&mdash;which accepted its first black undergraduates in 1963&mdash;to tell both a local and national story about the challenges that historically white colleges and universities throughout the country continue to face.</div>
</div>
<div class="simple-item-view-uri item-page-field-wrapper table">
<h5>URI</h5>
<span><a href="https://library.oapen.org/handle/20.500.12657/51885">https://library.oapen.org/handle/20.500.12657/51885</a></span>
</div>
<div class="item-page-field-wrapper">
<h5>Keywords</h5>Jim Crow; Black Power; black student activism; black campus movement; segregation; Black studies; HWCU</div>
<div class="item-page-field-wrapper">
<h5>DOI</h5>10.1215/9781478012955</div>
<div class="simple-item-view-date word-break item-page-field-wrapper table">
<h5>ISBN</h5>9781478010401, 9781478011422, 9781478012955, 9781478012955</div>
<div class="item-page-field-wrapper">
<h5>Publisher</h5>
<a href="/handle/20.500.12657/22279">Duke University Press</a>
</div>
<div class="item-page-field-wrapper">
<h5>Publisher website</h5>
<a href="https://www.dukeupress.edu/">https://www.dukeupress.edu/</a>
</div>
<div class="simple-item-view-date word-break item-page-field-wrapper table">
<h5>Publication date and place</h5>2021</div>
<div class="item-page-field-wrapper">
